00162 /* NumericRanges are used select a subset in a (multidimensional) variant array.
00163  * NumericRange has no official type structure in the standard. On the wire, it
00164  * only exists as an encoded string, such as "1:2,0:3,5". The colon separates
00165  * min/max index and the comma separates dimensions. A single value indicates a
00166  * range with a single element (min==max). */
00167 typedef struct {
00168     UA_Int32 dimensionsSize;
00169     struct UA_NumericRangeDimension {
00170         UA_UInt32 min;
00171         UA_UInt32 max;
00172     } *dimensions;
00173 } UA_NumericRange;
00174

00195     void     *data;
